ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for leaving us a review. We've not made any changes to the recipe of NESCAFÉ Espresso, we've only updated the jar design. If you're concerned about the taste of your coffee, please give one of the team a call on 0800 58 57 59 so we can look into this.

Results.ReviewText: i loved this coffee thought it was better than any other costa or takeaway coffee, but....... They've now changed the packaging and for some reason the coffee also.  It is not as strong now, before I used 1.5ish heaped spoons in a mug, now I am having to put 3 spoons in the get the same depth and flavour.  I'm not happy at all as this in turn means I have to purchase more - not happy at all nescafe change it back, now its just a weak pathetic coffee that is quite tasteless on a normal spoon full.  Could Nescafe please respond as to why they have done this
Results.Title: Theyve changed the packaging and the coffe!

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, thank you very much for getting in touch & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made to the packaging. We haven't made any changes to the recipe itself but we'll pass all your comments on to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText:
Disappointed to find that the new, presumably cheaper, packaging was accompanied by a new 'cheaper' recipe as well - that unfortunately is in no way as good as the original.
I've always found the 'original' product to be a superb Espresso product, that I've used almost exclusively for the past 2 - 3 years at least. The new recipe however is very poor in comparison. Net result = instead of ca. 1 - 2 jars a week, I shall now be buying a different product, and brand.
So disappointed - this is actually the only product review I have ever written for any coffee !
Results.Title: New Packaging, New Flavour = not for me !

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee for years and its simply the best. The powder rather then granules makes its taste more subtle and creates foam on the top while pouring water. Great and dense aroma. I put my espresso machine away long time ago!!
Results.Title: Best instant coffee ever

Results.ReviewText:
We have been buying this coffee for a few years now, it's the only instant coffee I like!
I like that it's a powder rather than granules and the taste is really very good for an instant coffee.
I use 1 heaped teaspoon to make a mug of coffee and it's perfect.
Whenever anyone comes round for coffee, they always ask what coffee it is as they really like it. I'm sure your sales go up every time I recommend it!
Don't ever stop producing this coffee please!!
Results.Title: Love this coffee!

ClientResponses.Response: It disappoints us to hear this but thanks very much for taking the time & letting us know!
